{{refimprove|date=July 2016}} {{History of Morocco}}
The "'''Azwafit'''" or "'''Azwafayt'''" ({{lang-ar|أزوفيت}}) is a tribe of bedouin (nomad) [[Arab]] origin.
== Etymologie == The word "Azwafit" ({{lang-ar|أزوفيت}}) is derived from the Arabic word "zfata", means "To protect from the Zfata". The Zfata is a group of people which claim false payments for the transportation of goods.
== About == The Azwafit are part of the greater [[Tekna]] confederation. Azwafit is a tribe which was accustomed to escort and protect caravans against the payment of "Ztata" or "Zfata", whence the name of Azwafit. Because they became part of a bigger Berberian tribe, the Arab subtribes are partially Berberised and speak Berber today.
The writer La Chapelle noted that Azwafits counted the following fractions: Ait Ahmed Ou Ali, Ahl Hayin, Mhamd Ait Ait El Khennous, Ait Messaoud Ait Boukko and Ida Ou Louggan.<ref>Tribes of Morocco. Azwafit tribe of Morocco.http://tribusdumaroc.free.fr/azwafit.php</ref>
