'''Frigyes Riedl''' (September 12, 1856 in [[Ladomér]] &ndash; August 7, 1921 in [[Budapest]]) was a prominent [[Magyars|Hungarian]] essayist, critic and literature historian. His most famous work is the monography of [[János Arany]], one of the most important 19th century Hungarian poets.

