[[File:Xavier Cortés Rocha (cropped).jpg|thumb|Xavier Cortés Rocha on 2018.]] '''Xavier Cortés Rocha''' is a [[Mexico|Mexican]] architect and urban planner. He was also rector of the [[Universidad Nacional Autónoma de México]] (UNAM) for a short time. He was born in [[Tampico]].
==Biography== Cortés graduated in architecture and later in [[urban planning]] at the [[Escuela Nacional de Arquitectura]] of the UNAM. He continued his studies in [[List of colleges and universities in France|Paris]]. After 1968 he taught at the UNAM. In 1999 he became Secretary General of the UNAM, and was interims UNAM president from 12 to 17 of November 1999. From 2001 to 2009 he was director of ''Sitios y Monumentos del Patrimonio Cultural'' of the [[CONACULTA]], as well as president of the [[Academia Nacional de Arquitectos]]. He is emeritus professor of the College of Architecture of the UNAM.
